<h1 class="doc-page-title">COMPASS Features</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">COMPASS provides a comprehensive suite of features for strategic delivery, compliance management, and performance monitoring.</p>

<h2 id="products">Products and services</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides a centralised view of all DfE products and services, integrated from the FIPS CMS system.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key capabilities:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Product catalogue:</strong> Browse and search all DfE products and services</li>
                    <li><strong>Product dashboards:</strong> View comprehensive information about each product including RAID items, metrics, and assessments</li>
                    <li><strong>Product linking:</strong> Associate RAID items, metrics, and assessments with specific products</li>
                    <li><strong>Status tracking:</strong> Monitor product lifecycle status and health</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0">Product data is synchronised from FIPS CMS and refreshed regularly to ensure accuracy.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="raid">Product governance</h2>
                
                <p>The product governance system provides comprehensive tracking and management of Risks, Actions, Issues, and Decisions.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risk management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk register:</strong> Maintain a comprehensive register of identified risks</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk assessment:</strong> Evaluate risks using impact and likelihood scoring</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk classification:</strong> Categorise risks by type (strategic, operational, financial, reputational, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk tiers:</strong> Assign risks to tiers (product, programme, portfolio, enterprise)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mitigation tracking:</strong> Document and monitor risk mitigation actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk ownership:</strong> Assign risk owners and maintain accountability</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Issue management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Issue log:</strong> Track all identified issues affecting products or services</li>
                    <li><strong>Issue prioritisation:</strong> Categorise issues by severity and priority</li>
                    <li><strong>Resolution tracking:</strong> Monitor issue resolution progress and timelines</li>
                    <li><strong>Impact assessment:</strong> Document the impact of issues on products and services</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Action management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Action tracking:</strong> Create and monitor action items</li>
                    <li><strong>Action sources:</strong> Link actions to their source (risks, issues, decisions, meetings, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Action ownership:</strong> Assign action owners and track accountability</li>
                    <li><strong>Due date monitoring:</strong> Track action due dates and completion status</li>
                    <li><strong>Action linking:</strong> Associate actions with risks, issues, and milestones</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Milestone tracking</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Milestone management:</strong> Track key project and product milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone linking:</strong> Associate milestones with risks, issues, and actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Progress monitoring:</strong> Track milestone status and completion</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeline visualisation:</strong> View milestone timelines and dependencies</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="card border-primary mt-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6">Best practice tip</h4>
                        <p class="mb-0">Always link RAID items to specific products and assign clear owners to ensure accountability and effective tracking.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="performance">Performance metrics</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS supports comprehensive performance tracking at both product and enterprise levels.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product performance metrics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Metric definitions:</strong> Configure custom performance metrics for each product</li>
                    <li><strong>Data submission:</strong> Product teams submit metric values regularly</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical tracking:</strong> View performance trends over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Target setting:</strong> Define and monitor performance targets</li>
                    <li><strong>Visualisation:</strong> Charts and graphs for easy interpretation</li>
                    <li><strong>Value types:</strong> Support for text, numbers, decimals, and percentages (0-100%)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio-wide metrics:</strong> Track high-level enterprise KPIs</li>
                    <li><strong>Aggregated reporting:</strong> Roll up product-level metrics to enterprise level</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link metrics to strategic objectives</li>
                    <li><strong>Executive dashboards:</strong> High-level views for leadership</li>
                    <li><strong>Value types:</strong> Support for text, numbers, decimals, and percentages (0-100%)</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="enterprise">Enterprise reporting</h2>
                
                <p>Enterprise reporting features provide strategic oversight across the entire product portfolio.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key features:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Enterprise metrics dashboard:</strong> View and submit enterprise-level KPIs</li>
                    <li><strong>Functional standards assessments:</strong> Conduct and track DDaT functional standards compliance</li>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio analysis:</strong> Analyse performance across the product portfolio</li>
                    <li><strong>Trend analysis:</strong> Identify patterns and trends across products and metrics</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="standards">Functional standards</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides comprehensive support for DDaT functional standards compliance tracking.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Standards framework:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Standards library:</strong> Browse all DDaT functional standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Themes and practice areas:</strong> Navigate standards by theme and practice area</li>
                    <li><strong>Criteria definitions:</strong> View detailed criteria for each standard</li>
                    <li><strong>Assessment workflow:</strong> Conduct structured assessments against standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Evidence capture:</strong> Document evidence of compliance</li>
                    <li><strong>Scoring and grading:</strong> Rate compliance levels for each criterion</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical assessments:</strong> Track compliance progress over time</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0">Functional standards data is synchronised from the DfE Standards CMS to ensure alignment with the latest standards framework.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="reports">Reports and dashboards</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides a range of reports and dashboards for different audiences and purposes.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Available reports:</h3>

                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Risks and issues report</h4>
                                <p class="small">Comprehensive table-based report showing all active risks and issues with filtering and export capabilities.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Analysis report</h4>
                                <p class="small">Visual analysis of RAID data including distribution by type, status, and product.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Product dashboard</h4>
                                <p class="small">Detailed view of a specific product including RAID items, metrics, and assessments.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Performance trends</h4>
                                <p class="small">Historical performance data visualised as line charts and trend indicators.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Report features:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Filter reports by product, date range, status, owner, and more</li>
                    <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Sort data by any column for easy analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Export:</strong> Export reports to Excel, PDF, or CSV</li>
                    <li><strong>Personalisation:</strong> Save report preferences and filters</li>
                    <li><strong>Scheduled delivery:</strong> Schedule automatic report generation and delivery</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="administration">Administration</h2>
                
                <p>Administrators have access to additional features for system configuration and management.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>User accounts:</strong> Create and manage user accounts</li>
                    <li><strong>Role assignment:</strong> Assign administrator or standard user roles</li>
                    <li><strong>Permission management:</strong> Control access to features and data</li>
                    <li><strong>User preferences:</strong> Configure user-specific settings</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">System settings:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk types:</strong> Configure available risk categories</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk tiers:</strong> Define risk tier levels</li>
                    <li><strong>Action sources:</strong> Manage action source types</li>
                    <li><strong>Metric definitions:</strong> Create and configure performance metrics</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic objectives:</strong> Define and manage organisational objectives</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Data quality:</strong> Monitor and maintain data quality</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit logging:</strong> Track changes and user activities</li>
                    <li><strong>Data export:</strong> Export data for backup or analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Integration monitoring:</strong> Monitor API integrations with external systems</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Additional features</h2>

                <h3 class="h5">Search and filtering</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Global search:</strong> Search across all RAID items, products, and users</li>
                    <li><strong>Advanced filtering:</strong> Filter by multiple criteria simultaneously</li>
                    <li><strong>Saved searches:</strong> Save frequently used search and filter combinations</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Notifications and alerts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Email notifications:</strong> Receive alerts for assigned actions, approaching deadlines, and high-priority items</li>
                    <li><strong>Dashboard alerts:</strong> See important notifications on the home dashboard</li>
                    <li><strong>Custom alerts:</strong> Configure personalised notification preferences</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Staff integration</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Staff autocomplete:</strong> Search for DfE staff members when assigning owners or contacts</li>
                    <li><strong>Azure Entra ID integration:</strong> Automatically populate staff details from the directory</li>
                    <li><strong>Team visibility:</strong> View all items assigned to team members</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Accessibility and usability</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>GOV.UK Design System:</strong> Accessible, user-friendly interface compliant with government standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Dark mode:</strong> Toggle between light and dark themes for comfortable viewing</li>
                    <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices</li>
                    <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Full keyboard accessibility support</li>
                    <li><strong>Screen reader support:</strong> ARIA labels and semantic HTML for assistive technologies</li>
                </ul>

